      "review_summary": "The PR adds OpenCode Go balance-only fallback support for Zen-only accounts, including billing server parsing, timeout/cancellation handling, snapshot changes, regression tests, and a changelog note.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for the PR defects by source inspection: balance-only snapshots expose only providerCost while the menu hides OpenCode Go providerCost when optional extras are off, and the required fallback calls an optional helper that swallows invalidCredentials. The original Zen-only behavior still lacks positive current-head live proof.",
      "review_followup": "- [P2] Human handling remains needed because current-head live Zen-only proof is missing and the branch still needs targeted code fixes around optional-off rendering and required-fallback auth propagation.",
